<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Finola on 11-10-2001 11:12 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I'm sure I'm going to get a lot of guff about this one but I'll state my opinion anyway. Personally I think it would be a great idea for clerics to get an invis spell, even if it's self only. That'd still be cool with me. One other person always stated that they are always dragging corpses for rezing. In those cases invis would be very useful if the particular mobs in that area can't see through invis. What would also be nice is maybe a few self only port. I think that would be great considering all the dangerous or even stupid places some people die. We are expected to rull all over hell and back to rez those people we could use some good spells to help us get to their corpses in a safe and timely manner. I know we'll never see the port spells, that much is obvious, but I would LOVE to see a regular invis spell even if it's self only. I know an invis spell is not too much to ask. And not all of us can get that mask you speak so highly of. Not all of us are quite ready to take on a lvl 53 anything.... and how do you get to OS? I've heard of it but I'm still somewhat new to the game (playing for about 6 months) so I am still learning.
It was also mentioned that we can just root and fear and run away. What if root and fear are resisted? Can you say "Bye bye cleric?" Yeah I thought you could. Any way after too much rambling my point is that clerics are in desperate need of an invis spell and I think we are well over due to get one. </TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
